author: Valerie Edwards For Dailymail.Com
title: DNA test shows Subway items may contain 50% chicken | Daily Mail Online
text: DNA tests show Subway's oven-roasted chicken contains just 50% real chicken Analysis revealed oven-roasted chicken sandwich contained 53.6% real chicken Subway's chicken teriyaki strips were found to have 42.8% real chicken Study also tested products from McDonald's, Wendy's, A&W and Tim Hortons All of those chicken products tested at least 84% real chicken, the study shows Subway Canada said the company 'cannot confirm the veracity' of test results Subway in UK and Ireland said the findings in the study 'are wildly inaccurate' Published: 16:16 GMT, 28 February 2017 | Updated: 18:21 GMT, 28 February 2017 63 shares
